# Security rules — Meavo org standard

Org standard (see STANDARDS.md §4 in meavo-agent-templates). Deviations for this repo are listed at the bottom.

## Auth at every layer

- Verify auth independently in: middleware (pages), the `(app)` layout, and API routes.
- Middleware passes `/api/*` through — never assume an API route is protected.
- This repo's auth gates:
  - Pages: `requireClockAccess()` in `src/lib/meavo-auth.ts` (called from `src/app/(app)/layout.tsx`; redirects to `/login`).
  - Admin API routes: `requireAdminApi()` in `src/lib/admin-api.ts` (throws 401 → `jsonError`).
  - Device routes (`/api/device/*`): `assertDeviceAuth(req)` in `src/lib/device-auth.ts` — kiosk sends `X-Device-Key` matched against `DEVICE_API_KEY`.
- Tool card gating: check `ToolCardAccess` for `CLOCK_TOOL_CARD_ID` (default `seed-clock-tool`, `src/lib/constants.ts`) at login AND on every authenticated request, so revocation in gateway Admin takes effect immediately. Never look up the card by `linkedAppKey` at runtime.

## Sessions & credentials

- NextAuth v5 JWT sessions (`src/lib/auth.ts`); session carries `user.id` via the JWT callback.
- Google OAuth is invite-only: `@meavo.com` emails only, user must already exist in the shared DB, and must hold the clock tool card (`src/lib/google-auth.ts`).
- There is NO credentials/password provider in this app — do not add one without an explicit decision.

## Routes & rendering

- Cron routes: `CRON_SECRET` Bearer auth on every `/api/cron/*` handler (see `src/app/api/cron/expire-pending/route.ts`).
- Health check: `GET /api/health` (`SELECT 1`), unauthenticated by design.
- `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` on the authenticated `(app)` layout and any DB-touching page.
- Never return stack traces to clients — throw `Error` with a `status` property and map via `jsonError()`.
- Security headers (`X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options`, `Referrer-Policy`, `Strict-Transport-Security`) are set globally in `next.config.ts` — keep them when editing that file.
- Kiosk TLS: firmware pins ISRG Root X1 via `API_ROOT_CA` (`firmware/include/config.example.h`); never ship a kiosk with `API_INSECURE_TLS 1`.

## Secrets

- No secrets in client code, comments, or committed files.
- Document env var names in `.env.example` only — never values.
- `firmware/include/config.h` holds WiFi credentials + `DEVICE_API_KEY` and is git-ignored; only edit `config.example.h`.

## Repo-specific deviations (pre-standard app)

- Middleware checks only for the presence of the session cookie (`src/middleware.ts`) — real verification happens in the layout/API gates.
- No credentials login, so no bcrypt or shared `LoginThrottle` usage.
- Session does not carry `systemRole` / `hrAccess` — access is tool-card-only.
- Device auth is a single shared static key (`DEVICE_API_KEY`), not per-device credentials.
